@Node "WHATIS_TurboTop" "TurboTop - What The Hell Is This? - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996 - Digital Design"

What Is @{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop@{ub}@{fg text}?
+-------------+

TurboTop is a Top 10 CPS Compilation System - Similair to my older programme
SuperCPS, written in rexx, which was both slow and nasty full of bugs. So
I decieded to TOTALLY re-write it in C and add some more features, thus
TurboTop.

TurboTop will only work if it finds a file in the T: directory called
"CPSRate_<linenumber>.Temp". A programme that does this is AsXPR v1.14+
by Andrew Scott, although look out for DigiXpr from me sometime this year :)

It examines this file for CPS Rate from the last transfer, be it either
an upload or a download, and will process the rates. If there is just 1
CPS Rate then this will be used, but if there is more than one CPS Rate
(batch) then TurboTop will calculate an average from these integers.

Once a suitable rate has been determined then the next thing TurboTop does is
load in the "TurboTopTable" for the current Bps (Baud) Rate of the online
user. If however a table for this Bps (Baud) Rate doesn't exist then TT will
create a default one to operate from. Fully automatic :)
Then this CPS is compared against all the others.. If you're higher then your
CPS is added to the table, if not then you get told this and the table remains
untouched.

It really is that simple, a nice effective, good looking, fast programme,
hang on - Are we talking about TRANSAMIGA here? ;-))

Your CPS Rate will also get a rating (in percentages), so you're final output
will look SOMETHING like this:

No | Cps Rate |    Date     |   Time   |       User Name      | Rating |Ln
---+----------+-------------+----------+----------------------+--------+--
o1 | 3361     | 06-Apr-1996 | 23:48:49 |Jay Tribick           |  186%  | 0

                                  -=[ Key ]=-

No        = Position
Cps Rate  = This Entry's CPS
Date      = Date This Entry Was Created
Time      = Time This Entry Was Created
User Name = The User Who Scored This Entry
Rating    = The Rating In Percent Comapred To The Bps (Baud) Rate Of That User
Ln        = The BBS Line Number This Entry Was Created On

                                  -=[ Key ]=-

@EndNode

