@Node "INSTAL_TurboTop" "TurboTop - How To Install TurboTop - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996 - Digital Design"

How Do I Install @{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop@{ub}@{fg text}?
+---------------------+

Simpleondo (Another one for the Oxford Neil p-).

Follow these simple steps OR use the provided C=ommodore Installer script.

1. Copy bin/@{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop@{ub}@{fg text} into your search path (reccomend "BBS:Bin").
2. Copy rexx/@{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop.Trans@{ub}@{fg text} to Rexx Dir (BBS:Rexx).
3. Copy rexx/@{b}@{fg shine}TTDisplay.Trans@{ub}@{fg text} to Rexx Dir (BBS:Rexx).
4. Copy text/@{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop@{ub}@{fg text} to Text Dir (BBS:Text).
5. Copy text/@{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop.ANSI@{ub}@{fg text} to Text Dir (BBS:Text).
6. copy docs/@{b}@{fg shine}TurboTop.Guide@{ub}@{fg text} to your docs dir (reccomend "AMIGAGUIDE:").
7. Edit your Main.Rx to include an entry for Displaying The Best CPS Rates, something like:

| TurboTop Display        10 -------- ttdisplay.trans

(Don't forget to edit your "MainMenu.ANSI"!)

8. Edit both Upload.Trans & Download.Trans and include an entry that states:

Call 'BBS:Rexx/TurboTop.Trans'

Near the end or wherever you like (If you're not too sure put it right at the end).

9. Edit TurboTop.Trans and TTDisplay.Trans to suite your system's setup.

Told yer it was simple ;-)

@EndNode

@Node "USAGE!_TurboTop" "TurboTop - Usage - (C) S.Gillibrand 1996 - Digital Design"

Usage
+---+

Self explanatory really!

	Usage:
		TurboTop <BBS Line> <Ratings Path> [Display]

Examples:

		TurboTop 0 Extras:TT  would use Line 0's CPS Rate against Extras:TT/<Bps>
		TurboTop 0 Extras:TT DISPLAY  would display a TT table to BBS Line 0

Very simple, all the rexx scripts handle it for you basically.

Report any bugs to @{"Me" Link "AUTHOR_TurboTop"} please.

@EndNode

